    {
      "id": "e7047918-e301-4c42-9917-db66ec67b16d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Increased digitalization of learning environments has allowed for the use of Log data to predict performance. However, these models requiure a larger-scale system that continuously collects and updates the model with new data. In order to have an easier system for data collection, the authors extract lecture questions from a Japanese University and use them to classify student grades.",
